# git-credentials format: one URL per line, password is the PAT.
# Git picks the matching entry automatically based on the host/path of any
# git command run inside open-terminal — no per-launch flags needed.
#
# Copy this file to ./credentials and add your real tokens:
#   cp infra/git/credentials.example infra/git/credentials
#
# Format:
#   https://x-access-token:<PAT>@github.com/<owner>/<repo>
#
# Examples (one per repo, or one broader entry per token scope):
https://x-access-token:ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx@github.com/myorg/repo1
https://x-access-token:ghp_yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy@github.com/myorg/repo2

# A single token that grants access to every repo a user owns can be written as:
#   https://x-access-token:ghp_zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz@github.com
# (git will use it for any github.com URL that doesn't match a more specific line)
